UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. SHAMIRAN ALOOJIAN et al., Appellees. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 9, 1931. Samuel W. McNabb, U. S. Atty., and Clyde Thomas, Asst. U. S. Átty., both of Los Angeles, Cal. Percy C. Church, of Fresno, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and JAMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for the respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
